               <msContents>
                  <summary>Letter in which the writer urges his brother not the neglect something.  Mentions a camel and may refer to building land. He also mentions books or documents and salutes a child "not under the evil eye"</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers; on the back an address</note>
                     <note type="general">16 lines; complete but some loss at upper left and abrasion on right</note>
                     <note type="general">Many holes</note>
                     <note type="general">The hand is an epistolary hand. The final farewell is in smaller characters but is probably by the same hand</note>
                     <note type="general">Space of 11.5 cm. left blank beneath the text</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
